WEBVTT

00:01.976 --> 00:04.278
<i>Nine years ago I witnessed</i>
<i>my mother's murder.</i>

00:04.280 --> 00:08.121
<i>I would've been killed, too,</i>
<i>if it hadn't been for Vincent.</i>

00:08.221 --> 00:10.739
<i>I was part of an experimental</i>
<i>Special Forces group.</i>

00:10.741 --> 00:14.059
<i>Their goal was to create</i>
<i>the perfect super soldier.</i>

00:14.061 --> 00:16.111
<i>But something went wrong.</i>

00:16.113 --> 00:17.312
You're him.

00:17.314 --> 00:21.833
<i>Being in any relationship,</i>
<i>it's a risk.</i>

00:21.835 --> 00:24.670
Dr. Forbes, it's about
something that you wrote.

00:24.672 --> 00:25.904
That was years ago.

00:25.906 --> 00:28.840
I have evidence that a
cross-species creature exists.

00:28.842 --> 00:30.592
I could do with a biochemist.

00:30.594 --> 00:33.061
I'd include you in all
aspects of the investigation.

00:33.063 --> 00:35.547
<i>My nurse, you might know her?</i>

00:35.549 --> 00:36.848
We grew up together.

00:36.850 --> 00:38.266
We were pretty close.

00:38.268 --> 00:39.267
They said you were dead.

00:39.269 --> 00:41.069
You should've
just given up on me.

00:41.071 --> 00:43.889
<i>I loved you.</i>

00:43.891 --> 00:46.475
Maybe I've been misreading us.

00:56.870 --> 00:58.437
Hi.

00:58.439 --> 01:00.939
Hey.

01:00.941 --> 01:02.774
Remind me never
to get shot again.

01:02.776 --> 01:03.825
Never get shot again.

01:03.827 --> 01:05.877
Come in.

01:05.879 --> 01:08.280
Thanks.

01:08.282 --> 01:11.950
Now put the
dumbbell down.

01:11.952 --> 01:13.618
Why do I get
the feeling

01:13.620 --> 01:15.470
that this is going
to hurt even worse?

01:15.472 --> 01:17.723
Give me your hands.
Come on.

01:17.725 --> 01:19.558
You need to work
on your flexibility.

01:19.560 --> 01:20.976
I don't remember
asking you

01:20.978 --> 01:23.294
to be my personal
physical therapist.

01:23.296 --> 01:25.147
Okay.
Okay.

01:25.149 --> 01:27.099
Slightly back, that's it.
Okay.

01:27.101 --> 01:30.402
Careful.

01:30.404 --> 01:31.737
You know, the first time
I got shot in Afghanistan,

01:31.739 --> 01:32.988
I couldn't sleep for months.

01:32.990 --> 01:36.408
Yeah, it's like
I'm sleepwalking.

01:36.410 --> 01:37.809
I can't do anything,

01:37.811 --> 01:39.411
and they've got me
on restrictive duty

01:39.413 --> 01:42.614
until I am physically
and emotionally up to par.

01:44.034 --> 01:47.035
And, again.

01:47.037 --> 01:48.787
You want to
answer that?

01:48.789 --> 01:52.023
Uh, no, it's okay.
I'll call her back.

01:52.025 --> 01:54.459
Ah, it's Alex.

01:54.461 --> 01:56.545
Really, Vincent,
it's okay.

01:56.547 --> 01:58.513
I don't mind.

01:58.515 --> 02:00.382
Uh, okay, thanks.

02:00.384 --> 02:01.850
Oh...

02:05.805 --> 02:07.773
Look, uh...

02:07.775 --> 02:09.191
Catherine,
the thing is...

02:09.193 --> 02:10.675
You... you don't
have to explain.

02:10.676 --> 02:12.778
She was your fiancÃ©e.

02:12.780 --> 02:16.314
You were planning
a life together for years.

02:16.316 --> 02:17.933
Six years
and an entire childhood.

02:19.786 --> 02:22.487
But... you and me...

02:22.489 --> 02:24.372
You and I are...

02:24.374 --> 02:26.158
You know,
I don't know what were are.

02:26.160 --> 02:27.692
We're kind of in no-man's-land.

02:27.694 --> 02:30.629
Yeah, I mean-I mean, we've
hardly even known each other,

02:30.631 --> 02:32.297
what, a few months.

02:36.035 --> 02:39.054
You know,
it's really none of my business.

02:47.730 --> 02:49.314
I'll be right out.

02:49.316 --> 02:51.766
Yeah.

02:51.768 --> 02:56.488
You know,
it's, uh, it's good you called.

02:56.490 --> 02:58.406
There's, um, there's something

02:58.408 --> 03:01.109
that I wanted to talk
to you about, too.

03:01.111 --> 03:04.262
I'll be all yours
if you just give me a sec.

03:13.039 --> 03:16.424
Is this what
you wanted to show me?

03:20.880 --> 03:23.849
No.

03:28.521 --> 03:31.389
This is.

03:41.901 --> 03:44.486
How am I supposed to compete
with six years?

03:44.488 --> 03:46.938
Not to mention the fact
that they grew up together

03:46.940 --> 03:51.493
and that she doesn't know all
the darker sides of him.

03:51.495 --> 03:53.795
But, if I say, hey, pick me,

03:53.797 --> 03:55.997
and ignore that
totally perfect, caring woman

03:55.999 --> 03:57.832
that you planned on spending
your life with,

03:57.834 --> 03:59.617
I am a total bitch.

03:59.619 --> 04:01.169
Aren't I?

04:02.255 --> 04:03.972
Are you?

04:03.974 --> 04:05.807
Don't "are you?" me.

04:05.809 --> 04:07.475
It's bad enough
that I am being forced

04:07.477 --> 04:09.344
to come here just to
get back to full duty.

04:09.346 --> 04:11.062
I could do without
the self-reflective crap.

04:11.064 --> 04:12.630
First of all, let me say

04:12.632 --> 04:14.432
that I am impressed
by your willingness

04:14.434 --> 04:15.633
to open up so quickly...

04:15.635 --> 04:17.736
Yes, I know
the mandatory routine.

04:17.738 --> 04:19.654
The sooner I spill my heart,

04:19.656 --> 04:21.973
the faster I get out of here.

04:21.975 --> 04:23.608
Second, what's mandatory,

04:23.610 --> 04:25.126
is for us to discuss the trauma
that you went through

04:25.128 --> 04:27.746
during the shooting,
not your boyfriend issues.

04:27.748 --> 04:29.331
Oh.

04:29.333 --> 04:31.449
Third, yes,
you would be.

04:31.451 --> 04:33.285
And that's okay.

04:33.287 --> 04:34.485
Sometimes in life
we need to be a bitch

04:34.487 --> 04:37.272
in order to get
what we need.

04:37.274 --> 04:38.707
And you're off to a good start.

04:38.709 --> 04:40.458
Sorry.

04:40.460 --> 04:44.462
I had enough therapy
to last a lifetime

04:44.464 --> 04:45.680
when my mom was killed.

04:45.682 --> 04:48.466
I know,
that is like throwing prime rib

04:48.468 --> 04:50.135
at a Rottweiler.

04:50.137 --> 04:52.270
Interesting choice of dog.
They're beautiful.

04:52.272 --> 04:53.888
And dangerous.

04:53.890 --> 04:57.175
No offense, Doctor...

04:57.177 --> 04:59.194
Oh, David.

04:59.196 --> 05:00.862
But I don't need a shrink

05:00.864 --> 05:02.731
to figure out
what my problems are.

05:02.733 --> 05:04.316
You mean running away from

05:04.318 --> 05:06.358
tough emotions and throwing
yourself into your work?

05:07.453 --> 05:09.120
I read your file.

05:09.122 --> 05:11.706
I hope it was a good read.
Mm-hmm.

05:11.708 --> 05:14.960
And from your file,
my conjecture is

05:14.962 --> 05:16.527
you lean on
your crutches:

05:16.529 --> 05:18.696
work, protecting people...

05:18.698 --> 05:20.582
Yes, I took an oath.

05:20.584 --> 05:22.300
To serve and protect.

05:22.302 --> 05:24.502
But who are
you really protecting?

06:10.433 --> 06:12.517
Catherine?

06:13.686 --> 06:15.303
Alex. Hey, hi.

06:15.305 --> 06:17.088
What are you doing here?

06:17.090 --> 06:18.473
I was just jumping
through hoops.

06:18.475 --> 06:19.757
Had to get a final evaluation

06:19.759 --> 06:21.393
before they return me
to full duty.

06:21.395 --> 06:22.727
What are you doing?

06:22.729 --> 06:24.362
I'm just heading home.
Running late.

06:24.364 --> 06:25.730
For... the gym?

06:25.732 --> 06:28.867
Oh, no,
it's, uh, change of clothes.

06:28.869 --> 06:31.953
I live a very glamorous life.

06:33.540 --> 06:34.956
Well, that's my ride.

06:34.958 --> 06:35.957
See you.

06:35.959 --> 06:38.543
Bye.

06:46.335 --> 06:47.919
<i>Someone please explain to me</i>

06:47.921 --> 06:51.339
how a guy who's unemployed,
never goes out,

06:51.341 --> 06:53.725
and is officially dead,
gets not one,

06:53.727 --> 06:57.011
but two smoking hot women
fighting for his attention.

06:57.013 --> 06:59.464
No, JT, the whole point
of going over there

06:59.466 --> 07:01.983
was to tell her
that I can't see her anymore.

07:01.985 --> 07:04.069
Because...

07:04.071 --> 07:05.320
because of Catherine.

07:05.322 --> 07:07.105
Kind of, yeah.

07:07.107 --> 07:10.141
I mean,
Catherine's life has

07:10.143 --> 07:13.244
never been the same since
she found out about me.

07:13.246 --> 07:14.496
And my secret.

07:14.498 --> 07:16.247
Neither has yours.

07:17.666 --> 07:22.003
You and Catherine, you risk
so much to keep me safe.

07:22.005 --> 07:24.172
And you don't want Alex
to take the same risks.

07:24.174 --> 07:25.507
No.

07:25.509 --> 07:28.209
Okay, but what if
I don't tell her?

07:28.211 --> 07:29.327
Vincent.

07:29.329 --> 07:30.795
Look, I know what you're going
to say,

07:30.797 --> 07:34.182
okay, but, JT,
to have someone look at you

07:34.184 --> 07:37.102
and not feel like
you've got this big secret

07:37.104 --> 07:38.586
that they have to protect,
you know.

07:38.588 --> 07:40.388
Like Catherine does.

07:40.390 --> 07:42.006
Yeah.

07:42.008 --> 07:45.860
But, JT, I... I loved Alex.

07:45.862 --> 07:49.614
You know, we spent our whole
childhoods planning everything,

07:49.616 --> 07:51.866
and then... ah.

07:51.868 --> 07:53.651
I don't know,
I guess I got afraid.

07:53.653 --> 07:56.204
And you don't think
Catherine's just backing off

07:56.206 --> 07:58.740
because she's trying
to do the right thing?

08:01.360 --> 08:04.546
How did I end up
on Catherine's side of this?

08:04.548 --> 08:05.797
My side of what?

08:05.799 --> 08:08.750
All you, my friend.

08:15.175 --> 08:18.092
What's this?

08:18.094 --> 08:19.594
I don't know how
to tell you this,

08:19.596 --> 08:21.846
but I ran into Alex
at the hospital.

08:21.848 --> 08:24.399
She was putting a bunch of
boxes into her duffel bag,

08:24.401 --> 08:28.603
and, it turns out that there
are a bunch of thefts

08:28.605 --> 08:30.321
being reported at that ward.

08:30.323 --> 08:32.222
You've been spying on her?

08:32.225 --> 08:36.394
I followed up
on something I saw.

08:36.395 --> 08:37.861
Vincent,
she's stealing medicine

08:37.864 --> 08:40.063
and supplies from the hospital.

08:40.066 --> 08:41.749
You don't actually know that.

08:41.751 --> 08:44.235
Okay.

08:44.236 --> 08:47.539
You can believe me, or not,

08:47.541 --> 08:50.074
but there is an open
narcotics investigation

08:50.076 --> 08:51.742
into these thefts,

08:51.744 --> 08:54.629
and someone else is going
to find out,

08:54.631 --> 08:56.598
eventually.

08:58.184 --> 09:01.085
Does she know?

09:01.087 --> 09:05.139
I mean,
does she know how careful

09:05.141 --> 09:07.692
she has to be with your secret?

09:08.600 --> 09:10.216
No.

